    <properties>
        <title>Apache James Server 3 - Protocols Configuration</title>
    </properties>

    <body>
        <section name="Core components Configuration">
            <p>James is an email server, and you can use various protocols to interact with it.</p>

            <p>This section presents protocolss configuration.</p>

            <p>
               Protocols includes:<br/>
               <ul>
                   <li><a href="config-ssl-tls.html">SSL/TLS</a>: Use of cryptography to secure mail protocols</li>
                   <li><a href="config-smtp-lmtp.html">SMTP/LMTP</a>: SMTP and LMTP configurations files</li>
                   <li><a href="config-imap4.html">IMAP</a>: IMAP configuration files</li>
                   <li><a href="config-jmap.html">JMAP</a>: JMAP configuration files. Only available for Cassandra guice wiring</li>
                   <li><a href="config-pop3.html">POP3</a>: POP3 configuration files</li>
                   <li><a href="config-fetchmail.html">FetchMail</a>: Allows download of email from other servers.</li>
                   <li><a href="config-sieve.html">Sieve</a>: User defined scripts executed upon mail reception.</li>
                   <li><a href="config-jmx.html">JMX</a>: Manage James via JMX.</li>
                   <li><a href="config-webadmin.html">WebAdmin</a>: Management REST API for James Guice wirings.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
        </section>

    </body>

